IDuplexSessionRouter Interface

Definition

Defines the interface required to process messages from duplex session channels.

In this Article

[System.ServiceModel.ServiceContract(CallbackContract=typeof(System.ServiceModel.Routing.IDuplexRouterCallback), Namespace="http://schemas.microsoft.com/netfx/2009/05/routing", SessionMode=System.ServiceModel.SessionMode.Required)]
public interface IDuplexSessionRouter

Remarks

This contract has the following settings:

  • Sessions are required.

Methods

BeginProcessMessage(Message,AsyncCallback,Object)

Initiates the asynchronous processing of the message.

public IAsyncResult BeginProcessMessage (System.ServiceModel.Channels.Message message, AsyncCallback callback, object state);
message
Message

The message to be processed.

callback
AsyncCallback

An asynchronous callback delegate that is invoked when the message processing has completed.

state
Object

A user-defined state object that is passed to the callback procedure.

Returns
IAsyncResult

An asynchronous result that can be used to poll or wait for results, or both; this value is also required when invoking stem.ServiceModel.Routing.IDuplexSessionRouter.EndProcessMessage*.

EndProcessMessage(IAsyncResult)

Finishes asynchronous execution of message processing.

public void EndProcessMessage (IAsyncResult result);
result
IAsyncResult

The asynchronous result returned by the call to stem.ServiceModel.Routing.IDuplexSessionRouter.BeginProcessMessage*.
